<subSubSection id="3B33453C3B0F0B20EB9F70B19805A1A9" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="87" pageId="2" pageNumber="85" type="comments">
<paragraph id="D5F96C4A4AF3898E1C12AFC99BF5986A" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="699BDA742F777CC2C6B96491581DA5C9" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="86" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">
The new material does not differ in any significant manner from the diagnosis and description of the species as provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="F71740DA7981EBCB1EAD9DF274384187" author="Engel, MS" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="237 - 247" refId="B5" refString="Engel, MS, 2009. The bee genus Chiasmognathus in the Arabian Peninsula (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Fauna of Arabia 24: 237 - 247" title="The bee genus Chiasmognathus in the Arabian Peninsula (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="24" year="2009">Engel (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, 
<pageBreakToken id="AE15452AFEB39985F7FA5D136ADB9F40" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" start="start">the</pageBreakToken>
sole Saudi male is not preserved in the best condition, with some distortion of the antennae and much of the body matted resulting from the mode of collection and subsequent preparation (
<figureCitation id="8D3A048CF64595F6010D0B8C7651BD5B" captionStart="Figures 4–10" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 4 - 10. Male of Chiasmognathus nearchus Engel from Namar, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. 4 Lateral habitus 5 Facial view 6 Dorsal habitus 7 Seventh metasomal sternum 8 Eighth metasomal sternum 9 Genital capsule, dorsal view 10 Genital capsule, ventral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11827" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Figs 4-6</figureCitation>
). Nonetheless, it was suitable for dissection and the terminalia are presented here for the first time (
<figureCitation id="CF43530D136DDA993F203A60325FB91D" captionStart="Figures 4–10" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 4 - 10. Male of Chiasmognathus nearchus Engel from Namar, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. 4 Lateral habitus 5 Facial view 6 Dorsal habitus 7 Seventh metasomal sternum 8 Eighth metasomal sternum 9 Genital capsule, dorsal view 10 Genital capsule, ventral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11827" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Figs 7-10</figureCitation>
) and for comparison with those structures depicted for other species (
<emphasis id="9BF42F5F81209DE972D5852601E43102" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">e.g</emphasis>
., 
<bibRefCitation id="921344058B366DEDCC57AA2A737FD592" author="Engel, MS" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Slovenica" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="113 - 121" refId="B1" refString="Engel, MS, 2006. A new genus of minute ammobatine bees (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Acta Entomologica Slovenica 14 (2): 113 - 121" title="A new genus of minute ammobatine bees (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="14" year="2006">Engel 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="65FA98407156AC9D20A9857C54BC4841" author="Engel, MS" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="169 - 174" publicationUrl="10.2317/0022-8567(2007)80[169:ANSOCF]2.0.CO;2" refId="B2" refString="Engel, MS, 2007. A new species of Chiasmognathus from southeastern Pakistan (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society 80 (2): 169 - 174, 10.2317/0022-8567(2007)80[169:ANSOCF]2.0.CO;2" title="A new species of Chiasmognathus from southeastern Pakistan (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." url="10.2317/0022-8567(2007)80[169:ANSOCF]2.0.CO;2" volume="80" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FE76C469582BBC53A400A21EDF6A0F27" author="Engel, MS" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="273 - 278" refId="B6" refString="Engel, MS, 2010. A new species of the bee genus Chiasmognathus from southwestern Niger (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 50 (1): 273 - 278" title="A new species of the bee genus Chiasmognathus from southwestern Niger (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="50" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3008167D8DB805AF074C81D67113B3A2" author="Straka, J" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="5" pageNumber="88" pagination="77 - 109" publicationUrl="10.3897/zookeys.218.3683" refId="B10" refString="Straka, J, Engel, MS, 2012. The apid cuckoo bees of the Cape Verde Islands (Hymenoptera, Apidae). ZooKeys 218: 77 - 109, 10.3897/zookeys.218.3683" title="The apid cuckoo bees of the Cape Verde Islands (Hymenoptera, Apidae)." url="10.3897/zookeys.218.3683" volume="218" year="2012">Straka and Engel 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="74B215025DE5039BB958916188CE1911" author="Engel, MS" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Melittology" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 7" refId="B7" refString="Engel, MS, Packer, L, 2013. A new species of Chiasmognathus from Kazakhstan (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Journal of Melittology 10: 1 - 7" title="A new species of Chiasmognathus from Kazakhstan (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="10" year="2013">Engel and Packer 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
